text.tspan: | “I filter events by location, cost, date.”
The event list in the low fidelity prototype was a list of events curated by Time Out to their users, once they click on a category they
see on the homepage, for example Best Halloween Events.
Since there are multiple events within a category and users already have certain decision criteria in mind as they search for events
such as time, location, and cost. After learning that users look through the list with those criteria in mind, we added a filter to help
them find the results they look for as searching through a list of events with no specificity is tedious and time consuming. Users
confirmed their satisfaction of the filter in the mid-fi and high-fi testing, therefore there were no additional iterations besides
